originalText.text: I really loved going here for a limited event “Harry Potter Potions Class”. I was concerned about the size of the venue with regard to what we were up to - but the event planners made it all work. The upstairs area is surprisingly sizable.

originalText.text: Cafe Victoria is the idyllic space for a quaint party or event. The space is is beautiful, with hardwood floors, huge windows overlooking a lovely tree covered block and a community garden, and tons of natural lighting.  The decor and furniture are elegant and charming, and there are many small details to admire, like the handcrafted candle holders. I helped host a baby shower at the venue and we needed to do very little set up or decoration to make the space feel warm, inviting, and festive. The owners were attentive and responsive and made sure we had everything we needed to make the shower a success.

originalText.text: I needed to film a scene at a cafe for my student film and this was perfect!  Great set up, great lighting, and very quiet!  Olga was always quick with communication and was flexible with scheduling.  Once the doors are open, she lets you do your thing and never intrudes but is available should you need her.  Highly recommend.

originalText.text: World Association for Children held an adoption event here recently and I attended as their adoption consultant. Having never been to the venue I got there early. It was there that I met Olga and Fr. Yakov who were extremely gracious hosts throughout our entire time there. The space is extremely comfortable and the atmosphere is very congenial. Every effort was made to ensure that guests were comfortable and that our stay was eventful. The families that attended found the location to be very convenient. Needless to say Olga went above and beyond the call of duty for our group and I would absolutely hold our next event here.

originalText.text: The light and airy 2nd floor room provided a congenial space for hosting the first birthday party for my godson, his parents, and family and friends.  A nice niche for buffet food service, and a banquette with tables and chairs provided plenty of seating, with open space for moving and mingling.
